title: Start
---
$c1: Continuity law is very clear until a patient survives the parts list.

-> $c2: The chip says this shell was collateral. I say it learned to walk away.
    $c1: Then we are arguing with a ledger that thinks breath is a rounding error.
    <<jump Close>>
-> $c2: Where does the claim start?
    $c1: With the debt desk. It always starts there, because debt prefers witnesses.
    <<jump Close>>
===
title: Sable
---
$c1: Continuity law is very clear until a patient survives the parts list.

-> $c2: The chip says this shell was collateral. I say it learned to walk away.
    $c1: Then keep saying it. The clinic records will not say it first.
    <<jump Close>>
-> $c2: Can you prove the patient survived transfer?
    $c1: Medically, yes. Legally, they keep moving the mouth of the word "patient."
    <<jump Close>>
===
title: Kade
---
$c1: They gave me a body with a stranger's debt still welded to the spine.

-> $c2: The chip says this shell was collateral. I say it learned to walk away.
    $c1: Then make it walk fast. They know the serials better than I know my new hands.
    <<jump Close>>
-> $c2: What do you remember before the shell?
    $c1: Cold light. Bad consent forms. Someone saying the debt would be easier if I slept.
    <<jump Close>>
===
title: Lio
---
$c1: Coolant first. Arguments second. Anyone venting steam near the rail gets billed.

-> $c2: The chip says this shell was collateral. I say it learned to walk away.
    $c1: Good. Say it away from the hot rail unless you want your argument pressure-cooked.
    <<jump Close>>
-> $c2: What is unstable in here?
    $c1: Everything with a pump, a signature, or a balance due.
    <<jump Close>>
===
title: MotherServo
---
$c1: A body is not a receipt. But receipts have teeth here.

-> $c2: The chip says this shell was collateral. I say it learned to walk away.
    $c1: Teeth can be filed. Names are harder. Find the name they are hiding under the debt.
    <<jump Close>>
-> $c2: Who benefits if Kade is property?
    $c1: Whoever can sell the cage and call the bird an accessory.
    <<jump Close>>
===
title: Morrow
---
$c1: Ownership loves a quiet signature. Bodies make useful pens.

-> $c2: The chip says this shell was collateral. I say it learned to walk away.
    $c1: Then you are sentimental. Useful, sometimes. Expensive, usually.
    <<jump Close>>
-> $c2: Did you write the claim?
    $c1: I notarized inevitability. People get angry when inevitability has my stamp.
    <<jump Close>>
===
title: Close
---
$c1: Keep the paperwork close and the exits closer.
===
